https://prez.dev/description.@value: The overarching categorization of vocabularies prepared by the Geological Survey of Western Australia (GSWA).

http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#defi.@value: Vocabularies related to the distribution and amounts of the chemical elements in minerals, ores, rocks, soils, water, and the atmosphere, and the study of the circulation of the elements in nature, on the basis of the properties of their atoms and ions; also, the study of the distribution and abundance of isotopes, including problems of nuclear frequency and stability in the universe. Adapted from Glossary of geology (Neuendorf et. al., 2011, 5th edition revised).
